I use to work in Geo seismic doing shot hole and I've packed more explosives than most people.  This explosion was not Ammonium Nitrate in my opinion. The compression was more like hydrogen expansion. The plumb was from dirt so I can assure you the blast came from underground blasting upwards as i view from the videos I've seen. I say this because it blew a "Smoke Ring" caused from the narrowing of the blast upwards. Now if the blast went out in all directions, it wouldn't have made a smoke ring. That smoke ring is like when you shape your lips like an "O" and puff the smoke out of the opening of your mouth. If you study blasts from a tube, they do this same effect. This blast was from underground.

it wasn't done by Isreal, you would've seen the airplane in the countless videos taken. there are tons of videos from different perspectives and none of them show an airplane and none have any airplane sounds. But in a lot of the other videos, they zoom in and it shows lights going off within the smoke, and I believe it was a firework explosion. Fireworks use gunpowder just like bombs do, but they are just toned down. With enough fireworks though, that gunpowder becomes a lot more than you would think and could easily cause this explosion. The reason there are no bright lights during the explosion is because fireworks have a certain amount of gunpowder and other chemicals in each rocket, but when there are thousands of them, and they all explode, 99% of the chemicals that create the fun lights are incinerated away, that's why at the beginning of the video, before the full explosion, you can see flashing lights going off from the fireworks before they are incinerated.

For those wondering, lemme clear some things up, the country is used to explosions that is true and sad Iknow, but they've already had to rebuild their port. Since the end of the Lebanese Civil War in 1990, the port has gone through a major updating and expansion program with the rehabilitation of existing port facilities, the construction of new administration buildings, and the construction of a new container terminal. During these expanding phases, they'd have explosions and things that don't work out anyway, so the port is pretty well known for being a destructive zone. Now then, the port has been said to have a warehouse with Ammonium Nitrate, a chemical. The smoke can only be that colour due to the chemicals inside it. The chemical was stored within a warehouse which is odd because statements from the Interior Minister in Beirut say that the chemical was not allowed anyway so they don't know why it was there, don't let false news of "fireworks" persuade you, those sparks were electric due to it being at a warehouse and a chemical which started the fire as if fireworks being kept in a facility would go up like that, blue sparks that look like lightning? make the correlation yourself, it's electric. So. that's about all the info I have from my research, live updates are being provided too so you never know I might be proven wrong, either way, #PrayForBeirut
